docs.lead_paragraph: LANSING, Mich. — When Elizabeth Warren took the stage at a rally Tuesday evening, she brought with her the kind of populist economic message that had roused working-class voters here during the presidential race three years ago.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders: Two Liberals Aiming for the Same Target

docs.abstract: Ms. Warren laid out a theme of “economic patriotism,” pledging to intervene in markets and invest $2 trillion in climate-friendly industries over a decade.
docs.snippet: Ms. Warren laid out a theme of “economic patriotism,” pledging to intervene in markets and invest $2 trillion in climate-friendly industries over a decade.
docs.lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts on Tuesday proposed an economic program of “aggressive intervention on behalf of American workers,” suggesting that as president she would invest $2 trillion in climate-friendly industries over a decade, create a new cabinet-level Department of Economic Development and even manipulate the dollar to promote exports.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Proposes ‘Aggressive Intervention’ to Create Jobs
headline.print_headline: Warren Outlines $2 Trillion Plan for ‘Economic Patriotism’

byline.original: By Astead W. Herndon and Patricia Cohen

docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey on Thursday announced a plan to offer clemency to more than 17,000 inmates serving time for nonviolent drug-related offenses on the first day of his presidency, an expansive use of executive power that would be the broadest clemency initiative since the Civil War.

headline.main: Cory Booker Proposes Clemency for Thousands of Nonviolent Drug Offenders
